results.name: Numerator in Moebius transform of A001790/A046161.
comment: Consider a lower triangular matrix T(n,k) defined by T(n,1)=A001790/A046161, k>1: T(n,k) = (Sum_{i=1..k-1} T(n-i,k-1)) - (Sum_{i=1..k-1} T(n-i,k)). The first column in the matrix inverse of T(n,k) will have the fraction A180403/A046161 in its first column.

The sequence considers the Moebius transform 1, -1/2, -5/8, -3/16, -93/128, ... of the sequence A001790(n-1)/A046161(n-1), i.e., assigning offset 1 to A001790 and A046161. - _R. J. Mathar_, Apr 22 2011
formula: Lambert series: Sum_{n >= 1} (A180403(n)/A046161(n))*x^n/(1-x^n) = x/sqrt(1-x). - _Mats Granvik_, Sep 07 2010
